text: Sphyraena sphyraena, the European barracuda, is a species of barracuda found in the Mediterranean Basin and the Atlantic Ocean. == Description == The European barracuda's body is long and compressed. It is a dark teal above and tan below. There is a chance of the fish having a yellow band. Sphyraena sphyraena also has scales covering both the margins of the preoperculum.
